1) What is the difference between integer and floating-point division? What is the operator used for integer division?
   What is the operator used for floating-point division?

A) Integer Division
	
	It is used to divide any 2 numbers and obtain the result as an integer.

	Ex : 10 // 3 ---> 9

	The // operator is used for integer division

   Floating-Point Division
	
	It is used to divide any 2 numbers and obtain the actual result in the form of decimals.

	Ex : 10 / 3 ---> 3.3333333333333335

	The / operator is used for floating-point division

